Dear C&C Forum Registrants,

Thank you for registering for our upcoming event, AI Frontiers in Healthcare and Medicine: Hype and Reality, on January 16, 2025.

We are excited to have you join us and look forward connecting leaders from various sectors with our faculty, students, and staff to discuss advancements in AI, data science, and multimodal data integration in precision healthcare. Get ready for a day full of insightful discussions and networking!

Here are the key details for the event:

Date: Thursday, January 16, 2025
Time: 9:00 AM – 2:00 PM
Location: Frances C. Arrillaga Alumni Center 326 Galvez Street Stanford, CA
Parking: Galvez Lot directions can be found HERE<https://www.google.com/maps/place/Galvez+Lot+(L-96),+Stanford,+CA+94305/@37.4335256,-122.1648679,15z/data=!4m15!1m8!3m7!1s0x808fbb28d19b8521:0x9fa2ade091cb2519!2sGalvez+Lot+(L-96),+Stanford,+CA+94305!3b1!8m2!3d37.4335256!4d-122.1648679!16s%2Fg%2F12jm3x3tl!3m5!1s0x808fbb28d19b8521:0x9fa2ade091cb2519!8m2!3d37.4335256!4d-122.1648679!16s%2Fg%2F12jm3x3tl?entry=ttu>
Program: We’ve got a fantastic lineup of speakers and a jam-packed schedule. View Event Program<https://dbds.stanford.edu/collaboration-and-careers-forum/>

Agenda:

  *   9:00 AM – 9:30 AM: Check-in & Light Breakfast
  *   9:30 AM – 10:00 AM: Overview of DBDS Initiatives & 2025 Vision with Department Chair, Sylvia Plevritis
  *   10:00 AM – 11:15 AM: Faculty Lightning Talks
  *   11:15 AM – 12:30 PM: Interactive Collaboration Forum (External Partners and Affiliate Program Members)
  *   12:30 PM – 1:00 PM: Lunch
  *   1:00 PM – 2:00 PM: Panel Discussion: "AI Frontiers in Healthcare and Medicine: Hype and Reality"

For additional information, please visit our website: https://dbds.stanford.edu/collaboration-and-careers-forum/

Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions or need further details.

From: pimedgroup <pimedgroup-bounces@lists.stanford.edu> on behalf of Ramzi Totah <rtotah@stanford.edu>
Sent: Thursday, June 5, 2025 10:57 AM
To: ibiisgroup@lists.stanford.edu <ibiisgroup@lists.stanford.edu>
Subject: [pimed] [ibiisgroup] Journal Club & Happy Hour
When: Thursday, June 5, 2025 4:00 PM-5:00 PM.
Where: 1701 Page Mill Rm 203


Yunhe Gao will be presenting "Bridging the Gaps in Vision–Language Models: From Diagnosis to Remedies”



Vision–language models excel at matching images with captions and power a new generation of zero‐shot and multimodal applications. Yet recent analyses reveal that global contrastive or caption objectives leave blind spots—poor intra‐modal clustering and weak patch‐level grounding. In this journal club, we’ll examine three analysis papers that diagnose these issues and two system‐level pretraining papers that propose remedies, highlighting how targeted alignment strategies can close these gaps.



Suggested Reading:

• Cross the Gap: Exposing the Intra-Modal Misalignment in CLIP via Modality Inversion (https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.04263)

• Two Effects, One Trigger: On the Modality Gap, Object Bias, and Information Imbalance in Contrastive Vision-Language Models (https://arxiv.org/pdf/2404.07983)

• Analyzing Fine-Grained Alignment and Enhancing Vision Understanding in Multimodal Language Models (https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.17316)

• Scaling Vision Pre-Training to 4K Resolution (https://arxiv.org/pdf/2503.19903v1)

• Perception Encoder: The Best Visual Embeddings Are Not at the Output of the Network (https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.13181)
